				<h2>How can I send a Compliment?</h2>
				<p>Following are the currently available ways to send compliments:</p>
				<ol>
					<li>From the drop-down Compliment Module available on most pages.</li>
					<li>By copying <strong><%= receiving_email %></strong> in an email you are sending to the Compliment Receiver.
						
						<p><br />
							- Skill of the Receiver you want to compliment must be entered in caret sign 
							(by pressing “shift + 6” on your keyboard), e.g.
						</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Sales^</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Customer Service^</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Project Management^</p>
						<br />
						<p>
							- The compliment type must also be entered in caret sign, e.g. 
						</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Professional to Professional^ OR ^Pro to Pro^</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Professional to Personal^ OR ^Pro to Per^</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Personal to Professional^ OR ^Per to Pro^</p>
						<p class="eg-text">^Personal to Personal^ OR ^Per to Per^</p>
						<br />
						<p>- Following is an example compliment sent by email:</p>
						<p><strong>To:</strong> Mike@complimentKarma.com, <%= receiving_email %></p>
						<p><strong>Subject:</strong> Any subject</p>
						<p><strong>Comment:</strong> Mike, Thanks a lot for all the help with ^Ruby on Rails^ web development. ^Pro to Pro^.</p>
					</li>

				</ol>
				<h2>Who can I Send / Receive compliments To / From?</h2>
				<p>As ComplimentKarma is available to for both Professional and Personal (i.e. Social) usage, so you can exchange compliments with anyone. Some examples of exchanges between users are as following:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Coworker to Coworker</li>
					<li>Company Employee to/from Company Customers, Vendors and Suppliers</li>
					<li>Individual Consumer to/from Company</li>
					<li>Individual Consumer to/from Company Employee</li>
					<li>Company to Company</li>
					<li>Friend to Friend</li>
					<li>Relative to Relative</li>
				</ul>
				<h2>Can I share my Activity & Achievement like Compliments, Badges, Trophies and Rewards etc, on other sites?</h2>
				<p>Absolutely yes, there are various options available for you to share your activity through email and other social networks like Facebook, Twitter and Google Plus etc.</p>
